The Deputy President of the Senate, Senator Ovie Omo-Agege, has congratulated the Olu of Warri, Ogiame Atuwatse III, on his 38th birthday anniversary. In a felicitation message on Saturday signed by the media adviser to the Deputy Senate President, Yomi Odunuga, he qouted Senator Omo-Agege as extolling the virtues of the paramount ruler of Warri Kingdom. The Delta Central lawmaker commended the wisdom of the royal father in administering his domain, consistently ensuring peace and development, and promoting a strong appetite for education and commerce among his people. “On behalf of my constituents in Delta Central, I congratulate the Olu of Warri Kingdom, Ogiame Atuwatse III, on the occasion of his birthday. “I commend His Royal Majesty’s dedication to the improvement of the lives of the common man in his domain, as well as his steadfast insistence on the peace, security, stability, progress and unity of his fatherland. “I pray Almighty God to continue to grant our revered monarch good health and more years of service to his people and humanity,” he said.